programme.title: The FBI Files
programme.desc: In the 1970's and 80s, people went to Alaska looking for a fresh start, to reinvent themselves, or to disappear for a while. Some of those disappearances weren't by choice.

programme.title: The FBI Files
programme.desc: On Mississippi's Gulf Coast, a Judge and his politician wife are murdered in their home. The killer left few clues. It looked like a professional hit, and the investigation led nowhere. But the FBI refused to give up.

programme.title: The FBI Files
programme.desc: In a city awash in narcotics the drug lords have all the power even over the police. Corruption in New Orleans grew like cancer, eating away at public safety and threatening to destroy the city. Crooked cops break the laws they were sworn to uphold.

programme.title: The FBI Files
programme.desc: When the small community of Noel, Missouri discovered their bank was robbed, they're shocked. When the bank president turned up missing, they're outraged. And when clues began to surface the facts were more terrible than anyone could have guessed.

programme.title: The FBI Files
programme.desc: They swept through six states like a plague, thrill killers acting without rhyme or reason. They targeted adults and young girls, kidnapping, and murdering. And in their rampage, they left plenty of clues, but moving targets are the hardest to hit.

programme.title: The FBI Files
programme.desc: A woman and her infant son vanish. The husband is frantic. The clues are scarce, but hopes linger, even as the hours and days tick by without a word. Was she on the run, or the victim of foul play?

programme.title: The FBI Files
programme.desc: Willow Springs, Illinois, seemed like any other quiet Midwestern community. But it was really one of the most corrupt places in the nation. This tiny village, nestled just outside of Chicago, was in the hip pocket of organized crime.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: A dog can be a dead man's best friend. Dogs have been trained to sniff out corpses, drugs, explosives, and missing persons. They're often the first to find the essential clue that sets an investigation in motion.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: For homicide investigators, it's a race against time as they track their deadliest foe: a serial killer for whom killing is the only way to feel alive.

programme.title: The New Detectives: Stolen Youths
programme.desc: A young girl playing in her yard in Spokane, Washington suddenly vanishes. In St. Louis another girl leaves to visit a friend. She never arrives.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Philadelphia's Vidocq Society, named after an 18th Century French detective, is one of the world's most unusual crime-solving organizations.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: When victims of murder know their killers, they are often caught off guard. But even the best-laid plans leave traces of the forsaken trust.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Investigators rely on forensic odontology to identify a body from a single tooth and to catch two brutal killers from their bite marks.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Weeks pass as forensic investigators search for even the smallest clues, only to find what they feared in their own backyard. In Canada, two people die suddenly of unknown causes, and their deaths may not be as coincidental as they first appear.

programme.title: Classic Doctor Who: Trial of a Time Lord
programme.desc: The Doctor realises that if he can speed up the Vervoids life span with light, they will decay. Using vionesium, he does so, unwittingly causing genocide in the process...
programme.sub-title: Classic Doctor Who: Trial of a Time Lord Part 12

programme.title: Classic Doctor Who: Trial of a Time Lord
programme.desc: The Valeyard's true identity is revealed and the trial aborted, but the Doctor and Mel must pursue his new enemy into the Matrix itself, where nothing is quite what it seems…
programme.sub-title: Classic Doctor Who: Trial of a Time Lord Part 13

programme.desc: Mel realises that the Valeyard has created a weapon within the Matrix that will destroy the Time Lords, and the Doctor is forced to rely on the Master for help...

programme.title: Doctor Who: Carnival of Monsters

programme.sub-title: Doctor Who: Carnival of Monsters Part 1

programme.title: Doctor Who: Carnival of Monsters
programme.desc: The Doctor and Jo realise that they are actually trapped in a loop on a miniaturised version of Earth in which the other ship passengers endlessly repeat their actions.
programme.sub-title: Doctor Who: Carnival of Monsters Part 2

programme.title: Doctor Who: Carnival of Monsters
programme.desc: Having escaped from the ship, the Doctor and Jo find themselves stuck inside the workings of a giant machine. Can they find their way out?
programme.sub-title: Doctor Who: Carnival of Monsters Part 3

programme.title: Doctor Who: Carnival of Monsters
programme.desc: The Doctor is reunited with the TARDIS and now full size, but Jo is still trapped within the machine. When the Doctor meets the operators of the Scope he learms that Jo is in grave danger.
programme.sub-title: Doctor Who: Carnival of Monsters Part 4

programme.title: Doctor Who: Day of the Daleks
programme.desc: When Sir Reginald Styles claims to have seen a ghost, UNIT is called in. The Doctor and Jo spend the night at Styles' house and become the target of an assassin.
programme.sub-title: Doctor Who: Day of the Daleks Part 1

programme.title: Doctor Who: Day of the Daleks
programme.desc: As captive of the guerrillas, the Doctor discovers they intend to change history. Jo is transported to the 22nd Century where she unwittingly gives vital information to the Daleks.
programme.sub-title: Doctor Who: Day of the Daleks Part 2

programme.title: Doctor Who: Day of the Daleks
programme.desc: The Doctor arrives in a bleak future where Earth is ruled by the Daleks and mankind is enslaved. Rescuing Jo, the two escape but the brutish Ogrons are in pursuit.
programme.sub-title: Doctor Who: Day of the Daleks Part 3

programme.title: Doctor Who: Day of the Daleks

programme.sub-title: Doctor Who: Day of the Daleks Part 4

programme.title: Doctor Who: Dragonfire
programme.desc: Mel and the Doctor are in for a cool reception on the trading colony Iceworld, where they discover excitable teenage waitress Ace, space maverick Sabalom Glitz, and legends of dragons and treasure.

programme.title: Doctor Who: Dragonfire
programme.desc: The time travellers, accompanied by Glitz and Ace, search the ice caves for the treasure which is supposed to be guarded by a fearsome dragon. Little do they are leading Kane straight to it.

programme.desc: Stephanie, CJ, and Caroline go on a girls-only junior lifeguard trip to Catalina which turns dire when two of the girls get trapped in a flooded cave. Meanwhile, a woman who dies in a car accident bequeaths an odd inheritance to Mitch…

programme.desc: Hobie's new friend Isaac is an angry kid who will do anything to get his father's attention. His risky behavior is a problem for the lifeguards. Meanwhile, Caroline meets a jockey who has lost the will to race after an accident.

programme.title: Baywatch
programme.desc: Logan borrows Cody's car without permission and has an accident, then lies to the police. Meanwhile, the Baywatch team settles an internal dispute with a paintball war and C.J. takes in an injured sea lion, causing problems with her roommates.

programme.title: Baywatch
programme.desc: Matt Brody returns to Baywatch and ends up trapped on a yacht with Neely when a group of ruthless pirates takes hostages. Meanwhile, Joey's past may jeopardize her adoption by Mitch.

programme.title: Baywatch
programme.desc: Logan and Caroline’s relationship hits a new low when Caroline returns his engagement ring, but things change when a baby is left in Logan’s possession. Meanwhile, Cody must overcome yet another setback to his Olympic career.

programme.title: Baywatch
programme.desc: Caroline blames herself for a teen's death in a fiery nighttime boating accident and goes through Critical Incident Stress. Pushing everyone away, Caroline begins partying to distract from her guilt. Can the team help her recover from her PTSD?

programme.title: Baywatch
programme.desc: A mysterious, unseen creature begins attacking beachgoers, and it is up to the Baywatch team to find the creature. Meanwhile, Inside Sports Magazine wants a lifeguard for their swimsuit issue. Neely and Caroline compete for the cover.

programme.title: South Park: Terrance et Phillip : de tempêtes en naufrages
programme.desc: Terrence et Phillip, les canadiens pétomanes, mettent fin à leur duo pour divergences créatives. Les garçons se mettent en tête de réunir leurs idoles.
programme.sub-title: Terrance et Phillip : de tempêtes en naufrages

programme.title: South Park: Asspen
programme.desc: Vacances à Aspen. Les gamins ont des ennuis avec des ados fous de ski et les parents vont vivre l'enfer de l'arnaque.

programme.title: South Park: La bande-annonce du nouveau Terrance et Phillip
programme.desc: Le visionnage d'une bande annonce se transforme en course contre la montre pour trouver une télé valable.
programme.sub-title: La bande-annonce du nouveau Terrance et Phillip

programme.title: South Park: Le veau, c'est rigolo
programme.desc: Les enfants se soucient du sort des veaux qui sont en réalité des bébé vaches torturés.

programme.title: South Park: Professeur Chaos
programme.desc: Butters est exclu du groupe des gamins. Excedé, il s'invente un alter-égo maléfique, le Professeur Chaos. Pendant ce temps, Stan, Cartman et Kyle mettent en place une sélection pour trouver un remplaçant à Kenny.

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: Aide Dora et Babouche à plonger dans le monde du magicien pour lui rendre sa baguette magique. Et en chemin, exauce les voeux de tous ceux qui fêtent leur anniversaire.

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: Totor participe à une grande course d'automobiles. Mais sa voiture est cassée! Aide-le à atteindre la ligne d'arrivée en compagnie de Dora et Babouche.

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: C'est le jour du grand débarras et Mister Truck emporte par erreur Sakado et la Carte à la déchetterie. Aide Dora, Babouche et Totor à les récupérer.
programme.sub-title: Le Coffre à Trésors de Totor

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: Catastrophe! Chipeur s'est introduit au pays des contes de fées et a volé les briques de la maison des trois petits cochons. Aide Dora et Babouche à rendre aux personnages de tes contes préférés tout ce que ce vilain Chipeur a chipé!
programme.sub-title: Dora Sauve les Trois Petits Cochons

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: Dora, Babouche et Cochonnette embarquent à bord du bateau des cochons pirates pour participer à la grande chasse au trésor des pirates. En chemin, il leur faudra chanter, danser, imiter des singes, donner à manger aux sirènes et parler anglais.
programme.sub-title: Aventures à Bord d'un Bateau Pirate

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: C'est le premier jour d'école de Babouche et Tico. Accompagne-les jusqu'à l'école avec Dora. En chemin, il te faudra trouver des tortues, compter des bananes et des noisettes, et apprendre de nouveaux mots anglais.

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: Babouche souhaite que des bananes pleuvent du ciel chaque fois qu'il prononce le mot 'banane'. Mais une fois exaucé, il trouve ce voeu bien encombrant. Dora et lui iront à l'atelier du grand-père de Roberto pour s'en défaire au plus vite.

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: Le vilain sorcier Malembruno a capturé Don Quichotte et le retient prisonnier dans son château. Rossinante, son fidèle destrier, appelle Dora au secours. Aide-les à délivrer le célèbre chevalier.
programme.sub-title: Dora va délivrer Don Quichotte Partie 2

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: Le vilain hibou a pris le pouvoir dans la Forêt Enchantée ! Aide Dora et Babouche à venir en aide au Roi Unicorn. En chemin, il te faudra reconstituer un pont, visser, chanter, sauter, et parler anglais, bien sûr !
programme.sub-title: Dora au Secours du Roi Licorne

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: C'est le jour du grand défilé d'Halloween. Et Petit Monstre est très malheureux car il n'a pas de costume. Aide Babouche et Dora à vite rejoindre le défilé pour lui en trouver un.

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: Dora et Babouche partent en vacances. Ils vont camper avec Diego et sa famille dans la forêt tropicale. Aide-les à boucler leur sac et à rejoindre le campement.

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: C'est l'anniversaire des Super Bébés. Aide Grandma à préparer leur gâteau, puis part avec eux à la poursuite de l'ours chipeur de gâteaux d'anniversaire !

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: Dora et ses camarades de l'école de danse s'apprêtent à donner leur spectacle de fin d'année. Mais leurs chaussons de danse sont restés à l'école de danse. Aide Dora et Babouche à aller les chercher.

programme.title: Dora l'exploratrice
programme.desc: Inspirés par Don Quichotte, Dora et Babouche veulent devenir chevaliers. Aidés par Rossinante, le cheval de Don Quichotte, et Donkey, un âne, ils partent au secours d'une princesse.
